33 // Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
34 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
35 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
36 // static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
37 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.

410 template <typename T>
411 class WeakCallbackInfo {
412  public:
413  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
414 
415  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
416  void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
417  Callback* callback)
418  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
419  for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
420  internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
421  }
422  }
423 
424  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
425  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
426  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
427 
428  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
429  void* GetInternalField1() const) {
430  return internal_fields_[0];
431  }
432  V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATED("use indexed version",
433  void* GetInternalField2() const) {
434  return internal_fields_[1];
435  }
436 
437  V8_DEPRECATED("Not realiable once SetSecondPassCallback() was used.",
438  bool IsFirstPass() const) {
439  return callback_ != nullptr;
440  }
441 
442  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
443  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
444  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
445  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
446  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
447  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
448  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
449 
450  private:
451  Isolate* isolate_;
452  T* parameter_;
453  Callback* callback_;
454  void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
455 };

458 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
459 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
460 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
461 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
462 // possible to request a second pass callback.
463 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

1199  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;

6042 struct JitCodeEvent {
6043  enum EventType {
6044  CODE_ADDED,
6045  CODE_MOVED,
6046  CODE_REMOVED,
6047  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
6048  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
6049  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
6050  };
6051  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
6052  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
6053  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
6054  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
6055  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
6056  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
6057 
6058  // Type of event.
6059  EventType type;
6060  // Start of the instructions.
6061  void* code_start;
6062  // Size of the instructions.
6063  size_t code_len;
6064  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
6065  Local<UnboundScript> script;
6066  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
6067  // code line information which is returned from the
6068  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
6069  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
6070  void* user_data;
6071 
6072  struct name_t {
6073  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
6074  // zero-terminated.
6075  const char* str;
6076  // Number of chars in str.
6077  size_t len;
6078  };
6079 
6080  struct line_info_t {
6081  // PC offset
6082  size_t offset;
6083  // Code postion
6084  size_t pos;
6085  // The position type.
6086  PositionType position_type;
6087  };
6088 
6089  union {
6090  // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
6091  struct name_t name;
6092 
6093  // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
6094  struct line_info_t line_info;
6095 
6096  // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
6097  void* new_code_start;
6098  };
6099 };

6106 enum RAILMode {
6107  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
6108  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
6109  // Throughput may be throttled.
6110  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
6111  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
6112  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
6113  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
6114  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
6115  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
6116  // in this mode.
6117  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
6118  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
6119  // turn off latency optimizations.
6120  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
6121 };

7639 template <class T>
7640 class Maybe {
7641  public:
7642  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
7643  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
7644 
7645  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7646  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
7647 
7648  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
7649  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
7650  return IsJust();
7651  }
7652 
7653  // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
7654  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
7655  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
7656  return value_;
7657  }
7658 
7659  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
7660  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
7661  }
7662 
7663  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
7664  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
7665  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
7666  }
7667 
7668  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
7669  return !operator==(other);
7670  }
7671 
7672  private:
7673  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
7674  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
7675 
7676  bool has_value_;
7677  T value_;
7678 
7679  template <class U>
7680  friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
7681  template <class U>
7682  friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
7683 };
7684 
7685 
7686 template <class T>
7687 inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
7688  return Maybe<T>();
7689 }
7690 
7691 
7692 template <class T>
7693 inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
7694  return Maybe<T>(t);
7695 }

8219 const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
8220 const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
8221 const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
8222 
8223 // Tag information for HeapObject.
8224 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
8225 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
8226 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
8227 
8228 // Tag information for Smi.
8229 const int kSmiTag = 0;
8230 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
8231 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
8232 
8233 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
8234 
8235 template<int kSmiShiftSize>
8236 V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8237  int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8238  uintptr_t tagged_value =
8239  (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
8240  return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
8241 }
8242 
8243 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
8244 template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
8245  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
8246  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8247  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8248  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8249  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8250  // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
8251  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
8252  }
8253  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8254  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8255  }
8256  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8257  // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
8258  // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
8259  // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
8260  // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
8261  //
8262  // CAUTION: The original code below:
8263  // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
8264  // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
8265  // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
8266  // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
8267  // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
8268  return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
8269  }
8270 };
8271 
8272 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
8273 template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
8274  enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
8275  static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
8276  static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
8277  V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
8278  int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
8279  // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
8280  return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
8281  }
8282  V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
8283  return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
8284  }
8285  V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
8286  // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
8287  return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
8288  }
8289 };
8290 
8291 typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
8292 const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
8293 const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
8294 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
8295 V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

8401  return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);

8404  V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
8405  bool value, int shift) {
8406  uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
8407  uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
8408  *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
8409  }

8949 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8950  typedef internal::Object O;
8951  typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
8952  typedef internal::Internals I;
8953  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8954  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8955  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8956  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8957  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8958  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType) {
8959  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8960  O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
8961  O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
8962  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
8963  }
8964 #endif
8965  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
8966 }

8970 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
8971  typedef internal::Object O;
8972  typedef internal::Internals I;
8973  O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
8974  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
8975  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
8976  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
8977  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
8978  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType)) {
8979  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
8980  return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
8981  }
8982 #endif
8983  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
8984 }
